o be a source of)   Blakey  .","English: habitational name from Blakeley Hall in Witton le Wear (County Durham), from Old English <i>blæc</i> ‘black’ + <i>hlāw</i> ‘hill’.","English: habitational name probably from Blakeley in Staffordshire, with the same etymology as 1 and 2 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Bleckley","meanings":["English: variant of   Blakely  ."]},{"name":"Blakley","meanings":["English (northern Ireland): variant of   Blakely  ."]},{"name":"Blakey","meanings":["English (northern): habitational name from Blackay in Lancashire. Alternatively, from Blakey (Moor and Topping) in Allerston (North Yorkshire), from Middle English <i>blake howe</i> ‘black mound’ (Old English <i>blæc</i> + Old Norse <i>haugr</i>)."]},{"name":"Bleakley","meanings":["English and northern Irish: variant of   Blakely  ."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Eleanor Blakely was born in 1619, in Otterton, Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married John Farre about 1640, in Otterton, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1619–":"1619–Surnud","1621–Male":"1621–Surnud","1644–1727":"1644–1727","1619–Female":"1619–Surnud","1644":"1644","1621":"1621","ABT 1640":"umbes 1640","1619":"1619","14 July 1644":"14. juuli 1644","1727":"1727","Otterton, Devonshire, England":"Otterton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Otterton, Devonshire, England":"Otterton, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1619–":"1619–Kuollut","1621–Male":"1621–Kuollut","1644–1727":"1644–1727","1619–Female":"1619–Kuollut","1644":"1644","1621":"1621","ABT 1640":"noin 1640","1619":"1619","14 July 1644":"14. heinäkuuta 1644","1727":"1727","Otterton, Devonshire, England":"Otterton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Otterton, Devonshire, England":"Otterton, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1619–":"1619–Décédée","1621–Male":"1621–Décédé","1644–1727":"1644–1727","1619–Female":"1619–Décédée","1644":"1644","1621":"1621","ABT 1640":"environ 1640","1619":"1619","14 July 1644":"14 juillet 1644","1727":"1727","Otterton, Devonshire, England":"Otterton, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of Otterton, Devonshire, England":"Otterton, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Eleanor Blakely est née en 1619, à Otterton, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé John Farre environ 1640, à Otterton, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée à Angleterre, Royaume-